resources.string:
	 The calculator is used to count the tasks forward and inverse kinematics for manipulators with serial kinematic structure. 
 	 If you want to calculate a forward task kinematics press the "Forward Kinematics" from the main menu 
 	 If you want to calculate a inverse task kinematics press the "Inverse Kinematics" from the main menu 
 	 In the application to write the join is used Denavit-Hartenberg notation. According to her are accepted coordinates systems and kinematic parameters. There are several steps to be saved data using this notation: 

• The Zi axes are drawn along the axis of rotation or the direction of advance; 
 • The Z-axis gripper are drawn parallel to the Z axis which precedes it; 
 • Place the center of the local coordinate system Oi, where the common normal axis Zi-1 and Z-axis intersects Zi 
 • Take Xi axes in such a way that they are common normal axis Z-1 and Z; 
 • The distance ai is measured along the axis X from the center of the local coordinate system Oi to the intersection of the axes X and Zi-1; 
 • The distance di is measured along the axis Z from the center of the local coordinate system Oi-1 to the intersection of the axes X and Zi-1; 
 • The angle of αi is measured between the axes Zi-1 and Zi axis Xi 
 • The angle θi is measured between the axes Xi-1 and X axis Zi-1. 

With so declared manipulator can easily enter the appropriate values to the table displayed in the application.
